    "answer": 3,
    "explanation": "R = ρL/A. When length doubles and volume stays constant, cross-sectional area halves. So R_new = ρ(2L)/(A/2) = 4ρL/A = 4R. Students often miss that both L and A change, or forget the volume constraint.",
